Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [telegram] <Hermes08> If you are using lite mode your seed is your way of accessing your wallet. You should take a copy of the private keys of the addresses that you have.... if you want to have the private key of each one of them individually...that gives you double security.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [telegram] <Hermes08> For instance if by any reason you loose your seed you could enter an specific address in a wallet with your private key only

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [telegram] <Hermes08> But there are different types of addresses in your wallet..your Bitcoin address is not the same as the one for Komodo

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [telegram] <Hermes08> so if you wish you can backup the keys of each individual public address by writing down  the private key.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [telegram] <Hermes08> The Komodo assetchains addresses share the same public address so having the private key for one Assetchain that you possess in lite mode gives you control of all the addresses that are KMD assetchains with that specific seed

[telegram] <Regnar> That's great to hear! It is certainly a bargain deal ;) currently Komodo is overhauling its brand and message and has brought on Ideas By Nature to facilitate this. Komodo is a decentralized project so most funds for things are crowdsourced or contributed from the lead developers own pockets, and I know there is a partnership announcement coming up, though I dont know how much marketing team is letting on before hand so I wont go beyond saying that (check out the discord channel for more info too).
There is also a lot of resources being built to help developers learn how to build on Komodo, and in various languages. It's pretty split apart right now (as is the nature of decentralized projects) but we are consolidating them for ease of use for developers.
